<br>
No Evils Allowed, is a big group defining rule. If you're not going to consult your guildmates, then you should expect fall out and comments about it and reprecussions as a result of that decision.<br>
<br>
That said, sometimes as a leader, you have to make decisions others may not like for the sake of your group. But that doesn't look like the case here. *shrug*.<br>
<br>
I don't think it was a cool thing to ban Eldratu from speaking out on her opinion on the matter, but it really has to depend on how Eldratu posted. If she swore like a sailor and called people a bunch of names, I'd of warned her about her posts and told her to be more civil before kicking her out. I wouldn't of just removed her because she disagreed with my decision.<br>
<br>
That said. I'm not the leaders of Elven Blades. But I'm glad I'm not a member of a guild that doesn't seem to value its members opinions.<br>
<br>
I don't know all the details, but again, if it is an instantaneous banning with no warnings , or no real bad language on her part, then I would completely disagree with it. I'd probably voluntarily leave such a guild.<br>
<br>
That said.. Mhordel is a great guy, and I'm sure he wouldn't want to see this kind of conflict. Its my guess that the person who banned Eldratu is very good friends with Mhordel and was probably overexhuberent in defending Mhordel and their right to have him as a member of the guild.<br>
