I am both mortified and facinated by the reception of the Community At Large, over my proudly taking the Elven Blades as family.<br>
<br>
Throughout my long life, I have ever strived to be a loveable troll, helping and seeing that my friends were happy and cared for.  Where my skills and talents were needed, I offered them.  My list of enemies is suprisingly short, and only contains people who have seriously wronged friends of mine.<br>
<br>
Since shortly after Christmass last year, I have been the image of a Feir'Dal after spending MANY insanely long hours making two for my IC wife (at the time) and myself, one crown each.  A real pain in the rear undertaking, back in those days.  So really, if ever there was a Elven Beastlord, in the minds of our small little world here, it would be me.  So to give the Blades a hard time for me, and state they are not as good Role Players as yourself, is sad and spiteful, imo.<br>
<br>
Lastly, as for the two people who spend so much of their time agonizing over me, Elderatu and Hether ( Hether has flamed me on the Fellowship Board ), both of whom I approached very kindly, when they unleashed some of the most hateful trash I have ever delt with back at me in tells, I had to laugh.  I know what IC and OOC is, and both genuinely hate me, without even knowing me, speaking to me, or meeting me.  Struck me as funny, since supposedly I am evil and they are good.  Ah well, I suppose the Nazi's were under the impression they were good, too.<br>
<br>
I will continue being me, and now being a part of an outstanding family that is the Elven Blades.<br>
<br>
I am still happy, and I wish you all the same. :)<br>
